The National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW) has disassociated its members from the mayhem that broke out at Diamond Hotel, Alakia in Ibadan the Oyo State capital, during which some men of the Nigeria Police were injured. Reacting to a news report in Sahara Reporters which linked the NURTW with the breakdown of law and order that took place in the hotel, the President of the union Prof. Tajudeen lbikunle Baruwa warned members of the public, especially reporters to stop confusing NURTW with Oyo State-owned Park Management Services ((PMS). “It is on record that the Oyo State Government in 20I9, proscribed our union on Oyo State. The government then inaugurated Park Management Services (PMS) and one Mukaila Lamidi (Auxiliary) was appointed as its chairman.   NDLEA arrests three traffickers with 48,000 tablets of…     Twin brothers allegedly defile 10-year-old girl in Anambra     Police arrest three suspects for allegedly, stealing,…   Read Also: Idumota crisis: NURTW condemns killings, unrest “Since 2019, PMS has been usurping our duties, activities and functions in Oyo State. It is, therefore, appalling and provocative to be linking our union to any illegality perpetrated by Mukaila Lamidi (Auxiliary)-led PMS in Oyo State.” - Advertisement - The NURTW boss appealed to members of the public, especially reporters to always crosscheck their facts before going to press. He threatened that the union will not hesitate to initiate legal action against any media house that continues to confuse PMS with NURTW.